textAnnotations.description:
No. 91
JOSEPHINE POLLARD.
62,2
BEYOND THE SUNSET.
4
4
所
DUET OR SEMI-CHORUS.
बही
Where gold-en glo-ries ev-er shine, Beyond the thought of day's decline.
Where clouds and darkness never come, My soul shall find its heavenly home.
And morning's lovely beams a - rise Up - on my mansion in the skies.
And Je-sus bids my soul pre-pare To gain a hap-py entrance there.
非
1 Be-yond the sunset's radiant glow, There is a brighter world, I know,
2 Beyond the sunset's pur-ple rim, Beyond the twilight deep and dim,
3 Beyond this des-ert dark and drear, The gold-en city will ap-pear,
4 Those gold - en portals ev-er shine Beyond the reach of day's de-cline,
FULL CHORUS.
W. O. PERKINS, by per.
Beyond the sunset's radiant glow,
!!
There is a brighter world I know;
radiant glow,
自
109
Repeat pp.
Beyond the sun-set, I may spend De-light-ful days that never end.
